## 13. Design Principles & Design System

### 13.1 Design Philosophy

Shiksharthi OS is an internal operations platform, not a marketing website.

The interface should prioritize:

* Fast information retrieval
* Low cognitive load
* High information density
* Minimal clicks
* Cross-device usability
* Mobile-first execution

Users should be able to answer any operational question within 10 seconds.

---

### 13.2 Visual Personality

The product should feel:

* Professional
* Trustworthy
* Warm
* Organized
* Modern

Avoid:

* Corporate enterprise aesthetics
* Excessive animations
* Overuse of gradients
* Neon colors
* Decorative elements without purpose

---

### 13.3 Color System

#### Primary Colors

* Primary Orange: `#F59E0B`
* Secondary Orange: `#FB923C`
* Light Orange: `#FED7AA`

#### Neutral Colors

* Background: `#F8FAFC`
* Card Surface: `#FFFFFF`
* Secondary Surface: `#FFF7ED`
* Border: `#E5E7EB`
* Divider: `#D1D5DB`

#### Typography Colors

* Primary Text: `#111827`
* Secondary Text: `#6B7280`
* Disabled Text: `#9CA3AF`

#### Semantic Colors

* Success: `#10B981`
* Warning: `#F59E0B`
* Error: `#EF4444`
* Information: `#3B82F6`

---

### 13.4 Color Usage Ratio

* 80% White
* 15% Neutral Gray
* 5% Orange

Orange should be reserved for:

* Primary actions
* Active navigation states
* Progress indicators
* Key metrics
* Alerts requiring action

Critical alerts must use red instead of orange.

---

### 13.5 Typography

#### Font Family

Primary:

* Inter

Fallback:

* Geist
* System Sans-serif

#### Type Scale

* Page Title: 32px / Bold / 40px line height
* Section Title: 24px / Semibold / 32px line height
* Card Title: 18px / Semibold / 28px line height
* Body Text: 14px / Regular / 20px line height
* Caption: 12px / Medium / 16px line height

---

### 13.6 Spacing System

Use an 8-point grid.

Approved spacing values:

* 4px
* 8px
* 12px
* 16px
* 24px
* 32px
* 48px
* 64px

Minimum spacing between cards:

* 16px

Minimum page padding:

* Desktop: 24px
* Tablet: 20px
* Mobile: 16px

---

### 13.7 Border Radius

* Small Components: 8px
* Cards: 16px
* Buttons: 12px
* Modals: 20px

Use consistent rounding throughout the application.

---

### 13.8 Elevation & Shadows

Card Shadow:

```css
0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06)
```

Hover Shadow:

```css
0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08)
```

Avoid heavy shadows.

Use borders and spacing before increasing elevation.

---

### 13.9 Icons

Icon Library:

* Lucide Icons

Rules:

* Use outlined icons
* Default size: 20px
* Navigation size: 22px
* Use semantic colors sparingly

---

### 13.10 Component Principles

#### Cards

* White background
* 16px border radius
* Subtle shadow
* Clear heading hierarchy

#### Buttons

Primary:

* Orange background
* White text

Secondary:

* White background
* Gray border

Tertiary:

* Text only

#### Tables

Desktop only.

Requirements:

* Sticky headers
* Sorting
* Filtering
* Search

Avoid tables on mobile.

Use cards instead.

---

### 13.11 Responsive Breakpoints

* Mobile: 0–767px
* Tablet: 768–1023px
* Desktop: 1024–1439px
* Large Desktop: 1440px+

---

### 13.12 Mobile Design Rules

Do not shrink desktop layouts.

Mobile interfaces must:

* Use bottom navigation
* Prioritize search
* Minimize typing
* Use cards instead of tables
* Support one-handed usage

Maximum taps per workflow:

3 taps

Minimum touch target:

44×44px

---

### 13.13 Motion & Animation

Animation duration:

150–250ms

Allowed:

* Hover states
* Skeleton loading
* Page transitions
* Expand/collapse interactions

Avoid:

* Parallax effects
* Complex animations
* Autoplay interactions

---

### 13.14 Accessibility

* Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1
* Support keyboard navigation
* Provide visible focus states
* Never rely on color alone for status communication
* Pair status colors with icons or labels
